    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>La Guardia's Traffic Jam</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ginny Donnelly letter says there is no reason that millions of air travelers should be inconvenienced to accommodate private jets, which should be barred from La Guardia airport at least in peak hours</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Port Authority Seeks to Limit Peak Flights at La Guardia'' (front page, Sept. 22):</p>
        <p>How many of the 371,000 takeoffs and landings at La Guardia Airport last year were by private jets?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Port Authority Seeks to Limit Peak Flights at La Guardia'' (front page, Sept. 22):</p>
        <p>How many of the 371,000 takeoffs and landings at La Guardia Airport last year were by private jets?</p>
        <p>There is no reason that millions of air travelers should be inconvenienced to accommodate the few super-rich people who have private planes. Private jets should be barred from La Guardia, at least during peak times.</p>
        <p>In addition, flights from New York City to cities a few hundred miles away and accessible by train should be capped, then gradually phased out as high-speed rail service improves.  GINNY DONNELLY  New York, Sept. 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
